UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="vu-box-container__inner anchor-boxes vu-box-container__primary vu-container no-gutter-rl overview" data-id="overview" data-title="Overview" id="overview"><div class="vu-container"><p style="font-weight: bold;">Overview</p> <div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p class="paragraph--lead">Propel yourself towards success with a career that perfectly aligns to industry demand. Learn how to identify, organise and analyse big data with Victoria University❛s Bachelor of Data Science.</p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu--additional-data item-type--basic-text"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text--white"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>In this data science degree, you❛ll learn to use specialised computational and statistical techniques to analyse big data and generate insights to tackle complex problems. These are pivotal skills for the 21st century, designed to meet the strong demand for data science professionals. </p><p>With industry-focused practices, real-world datasets, and hands-on tools, you will develop an in-depth understanding of deep learning, data management, data mining, and decision making. Throughout your study, you will learn how to wrangle, analyse, visualise, predict, and find insights into data to solve a host of real-world problems.</p><p>You will gain targeted expertise in:</p><ul><li>machine learning</li><li>deep learning</li><li>big data management</li><li>data mining</li><li>exploratory, predictive and prescriptive data analysis</li><li>data visualisation</li><li>business-oriented data analytics</li><li>cyber security-oriented data analytics</li><li>web, cloud and mobile application development.</li></ul><p>The Bachelor of Data Science is provisionally accredited at a professional level by the <a class="vu-link vu-text-link vu-text-link--external" data-print-url="https://www.acs.org.au/" href="https://www.acs.org.au/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Australian Computer Society</span><!-- --></span></a>. </p><p>Victoria University degrees are internationally recognised and help you find a satisfying career within and outside Australia.</p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></div><div class="vu--additional-data item-type--accordion-list"><!-- --> <div class="vu-courses--additional-data--accordion-list"><!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu--additional-data--accordion-list--items"><div class="vu-accordion-wrapper"><!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu-accordion__toggle-all"><button aria-label="" class="vu-button vu-button--tertiary vu-button--theme-light vu-button--size-small" data-v-6e5b367e=""> Open all </button></div> <dl class="vu-accordion vu-accordion--primary"><div class="vu-accordion__item"><dt class="vu-accordion__title"><!-- --> <button aria-controls="vu-accordion-4" aria-expanded="false" class="vu-accordion__button"> <span class="vu-accordion__button-text"> Learning outcomes </span></button></dt> <dd class="vu-accordion__content" id="vu-accordion-4" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-accordion__content-inner"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>On successful completion of this course, students will be able to:</p> <ol><li>Analyse core data science concepts applicable across various fields, including data exploration, data modelling, data visualisation, predictive analytics, quantitative analytics, industry-oriented data analytics, machine learning and deep learning;</li> <li>Apply and evaluate appropriate data science principles, contemporary technologies, and emerging AI tools, with intellectual independence and creativity to identify, design, implement, and evaluate data-driven solutions that address real-world enterprise problems;</li> <li>Synthesise decision-making methodologies to solve problems across a broad range of sectors, including ICT, government, banking and finance, retail, education, health, social network, and marketing;</li> <li>Demonstrate ethical awareness and professionalism in data science practices, with attention to legal, social, and compliance considerations in areas such as data privacy, integrity, and ethics in the field of data science, while demonstrating a commitment to lifelong learning and ongoing professional development;</li> <li>Integrate technical, analytical, communication, managerial, and interpersonal skills to support solution design, development, and project management in data analytics practice; and</li> <li>Collaborate effectively in diverse, interdisciplinary teams to deliver inclusive, industry-relevant data science projects.</li></ol></div></div></dd></div><div class="vu-accordion__item"><dt class="vu-accordion__title"><!-- --> <button aria-controls="vu-accordion-5" aria-expanded="false" class="vu-accordion__button"> <span class="vu-accordion__button-text"> First-hand industry experience while you study </span></button></dt> <dd class="vu-accordion__content" id="vu-accordion-5" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-accordion__content-inner"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>Our Bachelor of Data Science fosters a culture of practical experience through summer internships and final-year projects. </p><h5>Summer internships</h5><p>Each year, 50 students within the IT program will be offered <strong>paid summer internships</strong>, in collaboration with the Victorian Chamber of Commerce and Industries (VCCI) and SMEs. </p><p>The program has also established fractional FTE opportunities across various industry partners, such as Western Health (WH), VU ITS, and Her Creation Squad, among others. </p><p>Each internship is guided by a supervisor from the IT program and a mentor from the industry, ensuring a seamless and professional learning experience through these placements.</p><h5>Final-year projects</h5><p>Students leverage their data analysis and data management skills to devise real-world solutions through a final year applied Project units NEF3001 and NEF3002. </p><p>These units address industry-based learning of professional practices, on-campus WIL, and case studies. </p><p>Most projects are sourced from industry partners who play the role of clients, while supervisors assume the role of project managers. Recent industry partners for these projects include:</p><ul><li>Maribyrnong City Council (MCC)</li><li>Her Creation Squad</li><li>You Pack Logistics</li><li>Damaska Digital Australia</li><li>Curu</li><li>Raedan AI Pty Ltd. </li></ul></div></div></dd></div><div class="vu-accordion__item"><dt class="vu-accordion__title"><!-- --> <button aria-controls="vu-accordion-6" aria-expanded="false" class="vu-accordion__button"> <span class="vu-accordion__button-text"> Industry-focused curriculum </span></button></dt> <dd class="vu-accordion__content" id="vu-accordion-6" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-accordion__content-inner"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>VU provides a balance of theory and practical work to give you the skills to fast-track your career. </p><p>Our industry-focused curriculum prepares you with expertise in using theories, tools, and numerous marketable technologies, such as:</p><ul><li>mathematic and statistic fundamentals for data science</li><li>database system management</li><li>data science fundamental</li><li>big data management </li><li>data visualization</li><li>predictive analysis</li><li>machine learning and data mining</li><li>advanced data science, with a focus on text processing, computer vision, speech processing, time series, forecasting, anomaly detection, etc</li><li>IT profession and ethics in data science</li><li>project management in data science</li><li>data analytics for cyber security</li><li>data analytics for business</li><li>business system development</li><li>web/mobile/cloud application development.</li></ul><p>As part of your study, you will learn about and engage with:</p><ul><li>industry case studies and data sets</li><li>industry software applications and tools</li><li>assessment tasks </li><li>industry-based projects </li><li>industry-specific internships. </li></ul><p>Our Industry Advisory Committee ia comprised of employers and industry professionals with data science expertise. The committee contributes to the development and continuous enhancement of this degree, ensuring the program evolves alongside industry trends.</p><p>While you are studying, you will have opportunities to engage with industry guest speakers and leading data science researchers as part of:</p><ul><li>Work-Integrated Learning (WIL) courses</li><li>seminars</li><li>marketing events</li><li>industry awards</li><li>scholarship opportunities. </li></ul></div></div></dd></div><div class="vu-accordion__item"><dt class="vu-accordion__title"><!-- --> <button aria-controls="vu-accordion-7" aria-expanded="false" class="vu-accordion__button"> <span class="vu-accordion__button-text"> Take certifications with Amazon, Cisco, Microsoft &amp; Oracle </span></button></dt> <dd class="vu-accordion__content" id="vu-accordion-7" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-accordion__content-inner"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>In addition to our undergraduate and postgraduate courses, we also have strong partnerships with leading companies in the industry. These include but not limited to AWS, Cisco, Microsoft and Oracle.</p><p>Victoria University is an academy for a multitude of certification courses from these leading industries. This means, as our students, you will have the opportunity to study certification courses taught by seasoned lecturers and research academics within the IT discipline with discounted certification examination fees. </p><p>For more details, please visit the following links and contact your course chair.</p><ul><li>Amazon - <a class="vu-link vu-text-link vu-text-link--external" data-print-url="https://aws.amazon.com/training/" href="https://aws.amazon.com/training/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>AWS Training &amp; Certification</span><!-- --></span></a></li><li>Cisco - <a class="vu-link vu-text-link vu-text-link--external" data-print-url="https://www.netacad.com/academy/41944" href="https://www.netacad.com/academy/41944" rel="noopener" target="_blank" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Cisco Networking Academy</span><!-- --></span></a></li><li>Microsoft - <a class="vu-link vu-text-link vu-text-link--external" data-print-url="https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/education" href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-gb/education" rel="noopener" target="_blank" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Microsoft Education</span><!-- --></span></a></li><li>Oracle - <a class="vu-link vu-text-link vu-text-link--external" data-print-url="https://academy.oracle.com/en/solutions-curriculum.html" href="https://academy.oracle.com/en/solutions-curriculum.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Oracle Academy</span><!-- --></span></a></li></ul></div></div></dd></div><div class="vu-accordion__item"><dt class="vu-accordion__title"><!-- --> <button aria-controls="vu-accordion-8" aria-expanded="false" class="vu-accordion__button"> <span class="vu-accordion__button-text"> Supporting women in data science </span></button></dt> <dd class="vu-accordion__content" id="vu-accordion-8" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-accordion__content-inner"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>We support women and diversity groups in data science. We are proud to be part of the following groups:</p><ul><li>Stanford University Women in Data Science Networking</li><li>R Ladies network</li><li>CPA Australia Business Analytics.</li></ul></div></div></dd></div></dl></div></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></div></div></div>',
    total_course_duration = '3 years full time or longer for part time',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '35000',
    entry_requirements = '<div class="vu-box-container__inner anchor-boxes vu-box-container__primary vu-container no-gutter-rl entry-requirements" data-id="entry-requirements" data-title="Entry requirements" id="entry-requirements"><div class="vu-container"><p style="font-weight: bold;">Entry requirements</p> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu--additional-data item-type--basic-text"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text--undefined"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>Applicants for this course will need to meet the entry criteria outlined below. If you don’t meet the entry criteria, you may be able to gain entry by first completing a related course or unit(s). We call this a ‘pathway’.</p> <p> If you❛ve completed a qualification where English was the primary language of instruction, you may be eligible for an exemption of English-language requirements.</p> <p>In some cases, there may be additional entry requirements.</p> <p><a class="vu-link vu-text-link" data-print-url="https://www.vu.edu.au/study-at-vu/how-to-apply/international-applicants/entry-requirements-for-international-students" href="https://www.vu.edu.au/study-at-vu/how-to-apply/international-applicants/entry-requirements-for-international-students" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Learn more about entry requirements for international students.</span><!-- --><!-- --></span></a></p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></div><div class="vu--additional-data item-type--undefined"><!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></div><div class="vu--additional-data item-type--collapsible_section"><!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="collapsible-sections-container vu-courses--additional-data--collapsible_section"><div class="vu-collapsible-section"><div class="vu-collapsible-section-title" tabindex="0"><!-- --> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Entry criteria</p> <div class="vu-collapsible-toggle-icon"> <!-- --></div></div> <div class="vu-collapsible-section-content--parent" style="display:none;"><div class="vu-collapsible-section-content"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>Meeting the minimum entry criteria does not guarantee entry into this course. </p> <p>Completion of an Australian Senior Secondary Certificate (VCE or equivalent) including Units 3 and 4: a study score of at least 25 in English (EAL) or 20 in any other English (or equivalent).<br/> PLUS:<br/> A study score of at least 20 in Mathematics (any).<br/> OR:<br/> Completion of an Australian Advanced Diploma or Diploma (or equivalent).<br/> PLUS:<br/> IELTS (or equivalent): Overall score or 6.0 (with no band less than 6.0 in Listening, Reading, Writing and Speaking).<br/> OR:<br/> Completion of a Foundation course or equivalent.</p> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Special entry programs</p> <p>If you are from a disadvantaged or underrepresented social, economic or cultural background, you may be eligible for one of our special admission programs. These programs are designed to help you access education more easily.</p> <p><a class="vu-link vu-text-link" data-print-url="https://www.vu.edu.au/study-at-vu/how-to-apply/special-admission-programs" href="https://www.vu.edu.au/study-at-vu/how-to-apply/special-admission-programs" theme="primary"><span class="vu-link__inner"><!-- --><span>Learn more about special admission programs</span><!-- --><!-- --></span></a></p> <p></p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-collapsible-section__footer-text"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p></p></div></div></div></div></div> <div class="vu-courses--section--footer-text"><!-- --></div></div></div><div class="vu--additional-data item-type--collapsible_section"><!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="collapsible-sections-container vu-courses--additional-data--collapsible_section"><di