    course_description = '<div class="vu-box-container__inner anchor-boxes vu-box-container__primary vu-container no-gutter-rl overview" data-id="overview" data-title="Overview" id="overview"><div class="vu-container"><p style="font-weight: bold;">Overview</p> <div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p class="paragraph--lead">The International Foundations program at Victoria University (VU) is designed to prepare international students for tertiary studies.</p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <div class="vu--additional-data item-type--basic-text"><div class="vu-markup tide-wysiwyg app-wysiwyg vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text vu-courses--additional-data--basic-text--white"><!-- --> <div class="vu-markup__inner"><p>The university-preparation course offers a guaranteed pathway into the first year of select undergraduate degrees and diplomas at VU, providing you meet the course entry requirements.</p><p>The International Foundations course is comparable in standard to the Australian Year 12 curriculum, which is the final year of high school in Australia. It provides a supportive learning environment for international students as they adjust to living away from home.</p><p>The key learning areas are:</p><ul><li>mathematics</li><li>science and technology</li><li>the arts</li><li>business and legal studies.</li></ul><p>After succesfully completing the International Foundations program and meeting any course entry requirements, you will be provided guaranteed entry to VU undergraduate degrees and higher education diplomas.</p><p>This course is delivered at our <strong>City Campus</strong>.</p></div></div> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></div></div></div>',
